title: Sidewall, 1815–25
medium: Block-printed on joined sheets of handmade paper
description: a) Two putti holding up vase of flowers. Shades of brown on brown. To left is vertical stripe of brown leaves on blue; b) fragment of same paper as "a". On same ground as above, a diamond-shaped frame with sacrificial altar; c,d) duplicates of "b".

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall, 1815–25.
1815–25. Block-printed on joined sheets of handmade paper. Gift of Josephine Howell, Inc.. 1959-160-11-a/d.
